The paper deals with cooperative pathfinding for mobile agents, which is a problem commonly encountered in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm is based on a sampling-based approach, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also explicitly mentions multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and planning (cs.PL) as relevant areas of research. Therefore, these five categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
